choices.text: the signing of the Paris Agreement on Climate Change. This is a very important agreement for Kiribati as it is a small island developing state and is highly vulnerable to the impacts of climate change. The Paris Agreement is a legally binding agreement that was adopted by 195 countries in December 2015. It aims to limit global warming to well below 2 degrees Celsius and to pursue efforts to limit the temperature increase to 1.5 degrees Celsius above pre-industrial levels. The Paris Agreement also aims to strengthen the ability of countries to deal with the impacts of climate change. Kiribati is a party to the Paris Agreement and is committed to its implementation.
